'''''Napoleon in Russia: Borodino 1812''''' is a [[computer wargame]] written by Steve Krenek for the [[Atari 8-bit computers]] and published by Krentek Software in 1987.<ref name="mania">{{cite web |title=Napoleon in Russia: Borodino 1812 |url=http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-napoleon-in-russia_14915.html |website=Atari Mania}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Napoleon in Russia: Borodino 1812'' is a game in which the [[Battle of Borodino]] is simulated.<ref name="CGW41"/>

==Reception==
''[[Computer Gaming World]]'' described ''Borodino'' as "a welcome contriution to a much neglected, at least in computer games, era of warfare".<ref name="cgw198711">{{cite magazine | title=Christmas Buyers Guide | magazine=[[Computer Gaming World]] | date=November 1987 | pages=20 |url=https://archive.org/details/Computer_Gaming_World_Issue_41/page/n19/mode/2up |issue=41}}</ref> M. Evan Brooks's full review stated that "''Borodino'' is a solid effort. While it does not forge a breakthrough in game development, it is easy to learn, valid historically and entertaining. For those desirous of learning about Napoleonic warfare, it is recommended".<ref name="CGW41">{{Cite magazine |last=Brooks |first=M. Evan |date=November 1987 |title=Borodino: 1812 -- Napoleon in Russia |url=https://archive.org/details/Computer_Gaming_World_Issue_41/page/n37/mode/1up?view=theater |magazine=Computer Gaming World |volume=1 |issue=41 |pages=38â€“39}}</ref>

